steps.description:
Even before you get to the stage of adding delicious waffle toppings, consider spicing up the waffle mix pre-cooking. Some delicious ideas include:
Add fruit, nuts, herbs, spices, or cheese. Each of these additions gives the waffle a new taste twist. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d7/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d7/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Add cocoa for a chocolate waffle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/13/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/13/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Add crumbled crispy bacon to the waffle mix. The combination of salty bacon and sweet toppings naturally compliment each other. Add pureed fruit for strawberry, peach, mango, etc., flavored waffles. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a2/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a2/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make substitutions for water such as pineapple juice and chunks. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/63/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/63/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-2Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Be daring and move beyond the butter or maple syrup. There is an infinite variety of choices possible! Some of these include:
Add chopped fruit, including strawberries, or stewed fruit. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/04/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/04/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Add various flavors of ice cream. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Smother it in cream and chopped banana slices. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c6/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c6/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cover the waffle with chocolate. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4f/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4f/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Add cooked ham and egg. This is a great "cooked full breakfast" variant. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Sprinkle coconut over the waffle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c6/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c6/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet6.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Slather jam or jelly on your waffle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/40/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet7.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet7.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/40/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet7.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Shake powdered sugar over the waffle. While simple, it's a very effective flavor boost. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e9/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet8.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet8.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e9/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet8.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet8.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make a fruit salad waffle. Use as many different fruits as you'd like to add flavor and interest. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6a/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet9.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet9.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6a/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet9.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-3Bullet9.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Waffles made into various novel shapes can be a brilliant way to spice up a plain waffle. This technique can be especially handy for kids and for romantic breakfasts. Look for waffle shapes in your kids' favorite characters. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/78/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/78/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Heart shaped waffles make an interesting variation on the usual and are ideal for Valentine's Day or breakfast in bed for a loved one. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5c/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5c/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Any shape different from your usual shape can be fun. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/76/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/76/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Rather than simply placing the waffle on a plate as if that's all there is to it, try a fancy presentation. Layer the waffle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8e/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8e/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make a little mountain from the waffle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/21/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/21/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Take the time to make the cream into little shapes such as stars. It can look very effective when evenly balanced across the waffle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/eb/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/eb/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make a waffle ice cream sandwich. Use two waffles for the edges and fill with ice cream. Use a knife to cut and square off the ice cream. See also Make a Peanut Butter and Marshmallow Waffle Sandwich and Make a Peanut Butter and Apple Waffle Sandwich. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/17/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/17/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make a waffle "wrap". Fill with sliced meat and cheese, or roasted vegetables. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/09/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/09/Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Spice-Up-a-Plain-Waffle-Step-5Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
